<refsect2><title><anchor id="GtkMenuItem-activate"/>The <literal>::activate</literal> signal</title>
<indexterm><primary>GtkMenuItem::activate</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="void">void</link>                user_function                      (<link linkend="GtkMenuItem">GtkMenuItem</link> *menuitem,
                                                        <link linkend="gpointer">gpointer</link>     user_data)      : Run First / Action</programlisting>
<para>
Emitted when the item is activated.
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>menuitem</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>the object which received the signal.

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><parameter>user_data</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>user data set when the signal handler was connected.</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2><refsect2><title><anchor id="GtkMenuItem-activate-item"/>The <literal>::activate-item</literal> signal</title>
<indexterm><primary>GtkMenuItem::activate-item</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="void">void</link>                user_function                      (<link linkend="GtkMenuItem">GtkMenuItem</link> *menuitem,
                                                        <link linkend="gpointer">gpointer</link>     user_data)      : Run First</programlisting>
<para>
Emitted when the item is activated, but also if the menu item has a
submenu. For normal applications, the relevant signal is "activate".
</para><variablelist role="params">
<varlistentry><term><parameter>menuitem</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>the object which received the signal.

</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><parameter>user_data</parameter>&nbsp;:</term>
<listitem><simpara>user data set when the signal handler was connected.</simpara></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect2><refsect2><title><anchor id="GtkMenuItem-toggle-size-allocate"/>The <literal>::toggle-size-allocate</literal> signal</title>
<indexterm><primary>GtkMenuItem::toggle-size-allocate</primary></indexterm><programlisting><link linkend="void">void</link>                user_function                      (<link linkend="GtkMenuItem">GtkMenuItem</link> *menuitem,
                                                        <link linkend="gint">gint</link>         arg1,
